init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I see all the young people making foolish decisions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: All the things that I'd learned over the years—in school, in life, in self-discovery—were being ignored.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Little did I know that it was more than just ignorance.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: act strangely, their behavior more erratic than it was before they got the drug.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They never learned from their mistakes and they had no self-control.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I would become a doctor and give the old people immortality too.
